🇵🇹O MAPA DA LUA DE ANTES DE 1600
A ideia compartilhada da Lua como outra Terra, feita de montanhas e vales, teria provocado teorias muitas vezes surpreendentes. Se observarmos teorias mais antigas, por exemplo, as manchas lunares eram consideradas um reflexo da geografia terrestre da Terra. Outras teorias descreviam a Lua como uma espécie de nuvem com propriedades particulares, ou feita de cristal. No entanto, as grandes selenografias do século XVII, notadamente as de Hevelius e Riccioli, não discorrerão sobre a existência desse tipo de topografia acidentada.
t.me/sementesdeluz1

🇬🇧A MAP OF THE MOON FROM BEFORE 1600
The shared idea of the Moon as another Earth, made of mountains and valleys, would have provoked often surprising theories. If we look at older theories, for example, the lunar spots were considered a reflection of the Earth's terrestrial geography. Other theories described the Moon as a kind of cloud with particular properties, or made of crystal. However, the great selenographies of the 17th century, notably those of Hevelius and Riccioli, did not discuss the existence of this kind of rugged topography.

🇬🇧🐠💧Most cylindrical aquarium in the world breaks in Berlin, spilling 1 million liters of water 
 
A 16-meter-high cylindrical aquarium broke at the Dom Aquaree Hotel on Friday morning (16). More than 100 firefighters are working at the scene. 
 
A million liters of water was spilled, causing the release of 1.5 thousand fish and leaving two people injured. 
 
But the water did not stay inside the hotel. The authorities asked citizens to avoid passing near the hotel area, where a lot of water came out.
